          "question": "<p><a name=\"61075\"></a><div itemprop=\"text\"><p>Let \\( P-i \\) and \\( P_j \\) two processes, R be the set of variables read from memory, and W be the set of variables written to memory. For the concurrent execution of two processes \\( p_i \\) and \\( P_j \\) which of the conditions are not true?</p>\n\n</div><br><br><b>Operating System: UGC NET CSE | Junet 2015 | Part 2 | Question: 37</b></p>",
          "type": "single",
          "options": [
